6:
So this is the float I've been hearing so 
much about! It's a lot livelier than 
I thought it'd be.
9:
You've got it all wrong, Alk! This is just 
ONE float of many! Dwellings just like 
this one can be found all over the sea.
12:
Tie enough old boats together, and 
you've got yourself a float! Although 
the rise in unauthorized floats has 
been a real headache for the 
government lately.
17:
Why would the government be 
concerned?
20:
You can't tax 'em if you can't find 'em, 
right? But in the end, it's all about 
control.
23:
If we just sat on our dungbies and 
waited for those bureaucrats to 
actually DO something, half the 
population would be underwater!
25:
The people here quickly had to learn to 
survive on their own.
29:
That's admirable, but why isn't the 
government doing anything to help?
33:
All the government's focused on is 
trying to find a way to lower the sea 
levels again, but so far they've got 
nothing to show for it.
35:
Not like anyone has faith in them 
anyway—who knows what they're 
ACTUALLY doing?
43:
It seems that your crew has 
confronted someone.
48: What do you want, Navy scum?
50:
Yeah! Out of our sight, ya salty 
bastard!
53:
Okay, okay! Break it up! Didn't I tell you 
guys not to start a party without me?
56:
...And who do we have here?
You with the Gaean Navy? Look, 
despite what these boys have told you, 
we don't want any trouble, er...
60:
Lieutenant Trine of the Gaean Royal 
Navy.
62:
So these are the infamous Crimson 
Blades.
And you must be their captain, Marina.
65:
I'm honored you've heard of us. 
Speaking of which, judging by your red 
glove and sword, you must be—
68:
Wait a sec... Trine? As in Trine, The 
Reaper?!
69:
*gulp* Is it true she killed her entire 
platoon?
73:
HOW many times do I gotta tell you to 
not interrupt me! And stop believing 
every story you hear!
76:
Sorry, lieutenant. My boys can get 
a little rowdy at times.
79:
It's fine. But it is true... I was the one 
who let my comrades perish.
82:
...Geez.
Well, let's cut to the chase then. What 
business does a Gaean Navy officer 
have with my crew?
86:
I come asking for a favor. Could I sail 
with your crew?
89:
Hah! As if we'd ever let some Navy 
scoundrel ride with the Crimson—
97:
To find the reason behind the rising 
waters, I'll need to sail to the northern 
waters.
99:
However, I have no ship nor crew to do 
so. My superiors have decided to halt 
my investigation.
102:
So you thought to look for pirates, 
huh?
I wonder what your superiors would 
think?
105:
I am prepared to submit my 
resignation to the navy if needed.
108:
Regardless of my title or allegiance, 
I will remain steadfast in my mission.
113:
I see. You're not the sharpest cutlass, 
are you?
116:
Well? You heard her. What do you say, 
Stella?
121: She would be more than welcome.
125: Woohoo! Way to go with the flow, girl.
128:
You heard her. Now, I can't have you 
join MY crew for obvious reasons.
130:
Instead, you'll report to Alk and Stella 
here. Got it?
134:
As long as I can make it to the 
northern seas, that's fine with me.
138:
My name is Trine. Pleased to make 
your acquaintance.
145:
Letting a government boot on our 
ship?! Are you really sure about this, 
Cap'n?!
149:
Are you doubting MY judgment? 
Besides, this just makes things more 
fun! Right, Stella?
